Class
Description
CashRegister
The main class of the program, represents a cash register that sells individual items
Counter
This class is intended for counting quantities of programmatically defined data it functions similarly to a haskell monad
CounterContainer
this class represents a generic Counter container and contains some convince function to interact with them
HW2_kennamer
The main class of the program, represents a cash register that sells individual items
Item
This class represents a TYPE of item, it is intended to be used as a programmatic type, much like pythonic tuples.
Item.ItemCode
represents an item code used to uniquely identify each item contains several convenience functions for working with strings in the desired format
Item.ItemCode.MalformedItemCodeException
Custom exception that is called if a malformed item code string is given as an item code
ItemCounter
a convenient container class that ONLY contains items
ItemCounterContainer
an array of ItemCounters this class is a CounterContainer that FORCES the types input into it to be ItemCounters as apposed to generic counters
ItemCounterContainer.ItemCodeNotInContainerException
utility exception that is thrown when the given item is not found
ObjectMapInterface
a basic mapping function interface, intended to be used as an argument type for higher order functions that take 2d functions as an input
